Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.78,0:00:04.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The rhythm of the wind clears reasoning,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.72,0:00:06.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Always confirming that vital clue.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.59,0:00:08.22,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The secret behind the mystery is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.45,0:00:10.26,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We just have to get to the professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:12.36,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Recognizing that single truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.66,0:00:14.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A child with the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.73,0:00:16.39,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.25,0:01:53.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.38,0:01:54.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:01:57.27,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In my pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.17,0:02:00.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A clue to those men in black...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.47,0:02:05.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Later, on the Doc's PC,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.07,0:02:07.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll go through this disc from one end to the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:09.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.02,0:02:10.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.45,0:02:13.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think people change?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.77,0:02:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you're apart from them, do people's hearts change?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.59,0:02:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's pretty hard...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.09,0:02:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just waiting like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.98,0:02:36.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Shin'ichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-niichan{\r}'s probably just like you remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.16,0:02:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there's no need to worry...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.95,0:02:45.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, sometimes I wish you were Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.50,0:02:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must sound so dumb. What am I saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.94,0:02:58.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.43,0:03:00.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.47,0:03:01.79,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:02.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's really me...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.47,0:03:05.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.67,0:03:06.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't tell her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.83,0:03:09.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Until I figure out who {\i1}they{\i0} are...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.91,0:03:13.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Until I've taken them out...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.41,0:03:17.07,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I can't tell her who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:42.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.03,0:03:49.93,Title,,0,0,0,,Contact with the Black Organization: Negotiation Part!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.03,0:04:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crying again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.02,0:04:16.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.52,0:04:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're always crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:21.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Always?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.48,0:04:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.08,0:04:39.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:41.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just reminded me of someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.66,0:04:44.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A woman who looked a lot like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.77,0:04:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who pretended to be calm, but secretly cried all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.82,0:04:52.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A stupid woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.84,0:04:54.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A stupid woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.44,0:05:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.33,0:05:04.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.84,0:05:05.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.37,0:05:09.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I met him when I went to New York with Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.59,0:05:13.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was waiting for Shin'ichi in front of that old run-down building,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.37,0:05:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that guy came up to me and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.32,0:05:20.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Have you seen a Japanese man with long silvery hair and a beard?"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.63,0:05:32.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The building where the serial killer was hiding!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.16,0:05:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't think he's a bad person...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:36.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.35,0:05:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was with a guy who had "FBI" written on the back of his jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.37,0:05:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:47.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}FBI?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.42,0:05:48.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:52.38,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's the FBI doing here in Japan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.22,0:05:56.49,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh no, he's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.44,0:06:05.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go home, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.20,0:06:16.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But was he really FBI?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.20,0:06:22.78,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Somebody murdered that serial killer and made it look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.87,0:06:26.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If the FBI had that area closed off,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.58,0:06:28.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}there's no way they'd have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.15,0:06:29.92,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.19,0:06:36.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In the case when James{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was kidnapped, Haibara was getting bad vibes from him...{Haibara reacted to his presense... -blu}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.40,0:06:40.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What if he's the one who killed that serial killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.64,0:06:46.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Maybe he's involved in Haibara's past...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.41,0:06:51.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shuuichi Akai...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.83,0:06:56.88,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Could he actually be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.15,0:07:03.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what do you want for dinner tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.65,0:07:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sashimi? Tenshin rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.69,0:07:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your favorite beef stew?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.09,0:07:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't cook all three.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.99,0:07:13.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.70,0:07:17.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,I promised to play games with the professor.\NI'll be staying over there tonight.\N- Conan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.17,0:07:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I promised to play games with the professor.\NI'll be staying over there tonight."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.08,0:07:27.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Games again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.58,0:07:31.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jeez, such a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:41.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My priority right now is this disk, not Akai Shuuichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.76,0:07:44.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the diary of someone involved with the Organization...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:47.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Itakuro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} had actually met with Tequila.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.70,0:07:51.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I won't miss a single bit from this disk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I'll discover their objectives and their identities!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:07:59.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Their true identities!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.91,0:08:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shin'ichi, perfect timing. I've invented a new gadget for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.22,0:08:13.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, here's a pair of extra tracking glasses, so\Nyou don't have to recharge them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.39,0:08:15.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, where's Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.39,0:08:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}'s in the shower.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.96,0:08:21.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's great news.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.73,0:08:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shin'ichi, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.94,0:08:29.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You plan to go peep on her!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.27,0:08:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.84,0:08:37.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! You got your hands on a clue to them?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:39.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.38,0:08:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.69,0:08:44.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Haibara finds out, she'll get paranoid{literal: she'll worry unnecessarily},
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.12,0:08:46.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so let's go through this while she's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:48.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, two years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.55,0:08:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two years... ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.03,0:08:53.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bingo! Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,March 7...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.20,0:08:58.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man speaking the Kansai dialect came to see me unannounced.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.84,0:09:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He seems to want the operating system{system-soft = waseigo for an operating system, i.e. windows, linux, etc} I've been developing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.30,0:09:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when he found out my eyesight got worse and I'd abandoned it, he left.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.21,0:09:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was dressed in black from head to toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.37,0:09:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I never saw him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me that's all!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.92,0:09:23.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There doesn't seem to be anything written about that big guy in the diary entries afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.73,0:09:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So all I learned was that Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was developing some operating system that those guys wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.94,0:09:38.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this Itakura guy doesn't seem to be an organized guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.66,0:09:42.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, the spacing between diary entries is all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.41,0:09:45.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd never leave things this disorganized.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.95,0:09:52.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come to think of it, that guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.54,0:09:58.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He said that Itakura{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} would get angry if the papers on his desk were moved by even 10 cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.42,0:10:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it, Doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.39,0:10:05.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not that he's disorganized...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:07.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put the cursor in the space...{orig:If you select the space between each entry}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then drag it to invert it...{orig:by dragging the cursor while holding down the mouse button...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.42,0:10:15.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.40,0:10:17.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm wiped out."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.62,0:10:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"At this rate, I'm gonna be killed..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.61,0:10:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Invisible writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.88,0:10:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a method frequently used to hide information on internet homepages.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.19,0:10:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why would Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} do this in his own diary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.49,0:10:40.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He probably camouflaged it in case somebody looked at his diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.99,0:10:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi, by "somebody" you mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.09,0:10:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. It has to be them!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.28,0:10:59.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.56,0:11:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I finished my bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.80,0:11:17.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like he started using the invisible writing 10 days after the big guy's visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.76,0:11:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the next one says...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.90,0:11:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,March 17th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.32,0:11:27.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The pen on my desk had moved by 5 cm."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.30,0:11:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It looks like somebody went through my office."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,April 15th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.25,0:11:35.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Someone has broken into my house this time."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.78,0:11:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The police won't take me seriously..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.59,0:11:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"There was no sign of a break-in or anything taken, so I guess it couldn't be helped."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.45,0:11:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,June 11th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:50.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I changed my locks and installed hidden cameras, but it's no use."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.06,0:11:55.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,July 6th. "Who are you?! Show yourself!"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.87,0:11:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,December 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.80,0:12:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'm tired, and at this rate, will be killed in the near future."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.14,0:12:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,January 6th.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.49,0:12:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"To rid myself of the terror I'm feeling, I left a message to the intruder on the table."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.85,0:12:14.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I'll do what you want."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.91,0:12:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,January 8th. "They answered me sooner than I was expecting."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.65,0:12:24.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Instead of the message I'd written, the intruder had left a memo."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.57,0:12:29.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"An 'OK' written in red, along with a suspicious-looking phone number."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.49,0:12:36.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This red was probably blood... I wonder if they were trying to tell me that... I'll lose my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.98,0:12:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,January 23rd.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.84,0:12:44.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"After thinking for a while, I decided to call the number without telling the police."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.83,0:12:49.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Surprisingly, a woman answered the phone."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.00,0:12:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A presumptuous woman who talked as if she was a queen."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.67,0:13:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"She said she wanted to buy the OS I'd been\Ndeveloping for a large sum if I could finish it in a year."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.75,0:13:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"She's likely with the same group as the big man from before."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.11,0:13:10.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,February 13th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.96,0:13:13.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"They changed the contact method to e-mail."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.94,0:13:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I accepted their request, under the\Ncondition that they pay me in advance"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.12,0:13:24.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"and that they stop lurking around me."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.52,0:13:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,December 22nd.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.29,0:13:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I can't."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.32,0:13:31.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Like I thought, I can't do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.81,0:13:36.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I decided to stop developing this OS, not just because of my vision getting worse,"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.51,0:13:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"but for the sake of humanity."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.55,0:13:41.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the sake of humanity?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.95,0:13:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,February 9th.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:46.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The delivery date's coming up."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.18,0:13:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I've decided to hide the unfinished OS\Nand the check they made to me"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.33,0:13:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"near the computer at my\Ncottage and disappear abroad."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.72,0:14:02.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The e-mail stating when and where the delivery should take place"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.60,0:14:06.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"should arrive at midnight in five days. I have to get overseas by then."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.75,0:14:14.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This entry was written four days ago. It's\N9 PM, so the e-mail should arrive in three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.23,0:14:22.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems that Itakura{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} planned to escape abroad before seeing that e-mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.11,0:14:26.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like there's invisible writing even after the last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.40,0:14:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,February 10th.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.06,0:14:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Just what did they want to do with this OS?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.69,0:14:41.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I still remember the chilling words that the woman said during that first phone call."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Right."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.20,0:14:47.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I couldn't stand her presumptuous tone, so I flat out asked her"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.58,0:14:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Just who do you think you are?"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.68,0:14:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And she laughed at me and answered in English..."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.48,0:14:57.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We can be both of God and the Devil,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.25,0:15:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"since we're trying to raise the dead against the stream of time."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.01,0:15:05.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.35,0:15:08.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We are{can be} both {of }God and the Devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.77,0:15:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Since..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.22,0:15:15.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We're trying to raise the dead against the stream of time."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.34,0:15:18.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.48,0:15:19.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.49,0:15:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.67,0:15:24.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you reading a fantasy novel about witches or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.50,0:15:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. T-That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.04,0:15:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got addicted to some of these western novels being serialized on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.64,0:15:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what are {\i1}you{\i0} doing here, Kudo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.09,0:15:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, me? I'm—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.57,0:15:42.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He came to try out my new invention, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.14,0:15:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.83,0:15:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I call it the "Anywhere Ball-Shooting Belt".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.45,0:15:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it looks like a normal belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.98,0:15:55.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.66,0:15:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if you adjust the dial and press the button...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.86,0:16:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...a football pops out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.50,0:16:05.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.51,0:16:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be able to catch loads of criminals with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.58,0:16:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, more like a couple...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.18,0:16:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the nature of the rubber,\Nit will only hold its shape
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.26,0:16:18.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,for 10 seconds after it leaves the belt...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.99,0:16:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.53,0:16:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's very elastic though,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.94,0:16:26.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,depending on the amount of gas that's put in,\Nit can become as large as an ad balloon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.97,0:16:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's unbelievable!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.37,0:16:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.76,0:16:33.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.98,0:16:38.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now what do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.00,0:16:41.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we go to Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cottage, we get that operating system,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.90,0:16:49.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we'll use the computer there to receive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The e-mail that they'll send at midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:01.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cottage was in Gunma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.27,0:17:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle asked the person from the game company who hired him to look for Itakura-san
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.44,0:17:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,about his house, his cottage, and the acquaintances where he might be hiding out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.14,0:17:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is this really a good idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.59,0:17:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if they've set up an ambush for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.44,0:17:21.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} made them promise they wouldn't follow him around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.23,0:17:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd never break a promise they made to a guy who's so paranoid that he noticed
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.38,0:17:34.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when a pen was moved 5 cm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they'd angered him before the OS was done, their efforts would've been for naught.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.96,0:17:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happens if the news of Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder comes up on the TV or radio?{3-liner?}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.01,0:17:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's fine for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.01,0:17:53.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been checking the radio,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.34,0:17:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but all they've been talking about is the jewel thieves on the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.52,0:18:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What worries me the most are those words at the end of the diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.77,0:18:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.40,0:18:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"We are{can be} both {of }God and the Devil,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.68,0:18:11.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,since we're trying to raise the dead against the stream of time."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.93,0:18:17.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Doc...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.63,0:18:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me the poison Haibara was working on was actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.15,0:18:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.61,0:18:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meant to make zombies?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.09,0:18:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be impatient. {line from 131'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.98,0:18:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People can't go against the stream of time. {line from 131'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.07,0:18:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they try to force it... {line from 131'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:37.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...they will be punished. {line from 131'}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.33,0:18:39.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.84,0:18:42.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What does she mean by "punished"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.31,0:18:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.03,0:18:53.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, how are we going to get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.00,0:19:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where'd you get that key?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.73,0:19:02.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hidden behind the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.63,0:19:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember what the diary said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A friend who I hadn't seen in five years called me from my cottage."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.47,0:19:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the key was hidden somewhere so that his friends could come here when they wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.81,0:19:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't this dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.31,0:19:26.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he left this here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.09,0:19:33.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because they'd never imagine that he'd hide the OS they wanted in an unprotected place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.78,0:19:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if he doesn't receive the e-mail they're going to send,{orig:And they're sending the e-mail here,}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{so if nobody receives it, }they'll eventually come looking for Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.37,0:19:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they'll find the OS and the check.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.19,0:19:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} could sever his ties with them without needing to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.38,0:19:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.59,0:19:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shin'ichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.16,0:19:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost time...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.51,0:19:53.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.22,0:19:58.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come on, men in black.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:20:01.39,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Come out, you filthy rats!{Let me see your filthy tails!}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.18,0:20:04.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The e-mail's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.65,0:20:06.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Okay, let's open it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.36,0:20:10.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A password?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.15,0:20:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The count keeps going down!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.28,0:20:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.72,0:20:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-The e-mail's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.96,0:20:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.58,0:20:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's rigged so that if you don't open it immediately, it'll disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.46,0:20:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.66,0:20:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you think they know the e-mail wasn't opened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.97,0:20:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.77,0:20:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not only that, they may even know it came from this computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.64,0:20:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do we do? They may figure out that\Nsomething happened to Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.81,0:20:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.38,0:20:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.49,0:21:03.72,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}At this moment, we can't come to the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.71,0:20:58.71,Signs,,0,0,0,,Incoming Call\NNumber withheld
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:14.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Incoming Call\NNumber withheld
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.72,0:21:08.12,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Please leave a message after the beep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:14.20,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yo, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.26,0:21:17.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Vodka!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.47,0:21:20.16,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You're there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.16,0:21:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've been discovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.96,0:21:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They know we failed to open the e-mail in this cottage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.51,0:21:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe they've been watching this cottage without Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} realizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.56,0:21:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.43,0:21:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was almost certain that they wouldn't expect Itakura{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to open the mail here,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.20,0:21:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the insecurity of this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.42,0:21:44.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.56,0:21:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, how are we going to escape?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:48.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Incoming Call\NNumber withheld
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.09,0:21:48.92,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.62,0:21:53.35,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know you're in that cottage!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.91,0:21:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.28,0:21:59.92,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You better pick up the phone, Itakura{\rHonorifics - Radio\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.31,0:22:01.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,Incoming Call\NNumber withheld
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.06,0:22:04.61,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, what's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.90,0:22:10.10,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You hear me?! Hey!
